  "ciliary_role": "Regulates early embryonic axial rotation, anteroposterior and dorsoventral patterning in mice and is required for mainte nce of a normal ciliary structure (22939636). Required for assembly of full-length centrioles through its STIL- RTTN interaction, it also serves as an upstream effector of CEP295 (28811500). Centrosomal protein possibly involved in centriolar elongation and ciliogenesis. Mutations cause polymicrogyria (30879067) and missense or splicing variants have been found in patients with microcephaly (29967526).",
